{"word":"κάλαμος","slug":"κάλαμος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ϰάλαμος, οῦ, ὁ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ IE\">IE</a>, <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Lat.\">Lat.</a> calamus ‘reed, cane’] ‘stem of a tall grass’, <b>reed, cane<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> growing plant <b><a href='B:470 11:7'>Mt 11:7</a>; <a href='B:470 12:20'>12:20</a>; <a href='B:490 7:24'>Lk 7:24</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> cut stem <b><a href='B:470 27:30'>Mt 27:30</a>, <a href='B:470 27:48'>48</a>; <a href='B:480 15:19'>Mk 15:19</a>, <a href='B:480 15:36'>36</a>;</b> in imagery of a scepter <b><a href='B:470 27:29'>Mt 27:29</a>;</b> as writing instrument reed (pen) <b><a href='B:710 1:1'>3 J 13</a>;</b> as device for measuring reed (measure) <b><a href='B:730 11:1'>Rv 11:1</a>; <a href='B:730 21:15'>21:15f</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:καλάμη\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:καλέω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}